      <h2>
       The Public Connection
      </h2>
      <h4>
       "
       <em>
        Earth views of space and space views of Earth
       </em>
       "
      </h4>
      <p>
       Rice University has been a leader in Education and Public Outreach efforts for more than 25 years, through its many major initiatives, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
       <li>
        The Teacher Research Program (1988-91, NSF)
       </li>
       <li>
        Summer Solar Institute, 1992 (Eisenhower Foundation)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://earth.rice.edu/">
         The Public Connection
        </a>
        (funded by the Digital Library Program, NASA, 1994-1998)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="mtpe/">
         Museums Teaching Planet Earth
        </a>
        (funded by the ESIP Program, NASA, 1999-2004)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://space.rice.edu/IMAGE/">
         Outreach for the IMAGE mission
        </a>
        :  "POETRY" (2000-2006)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="immersive_earth/">
         Immersive Earth Program
        </a>
        (funded by the REASoN Program, NASA, 2004-2010)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://space.rice.edu/Cluster/">
         Outreach for the Cluster Mission
        </a>
        (2006 – 2011)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://mms.rice.edu/">
         Outreach for the MMS Mission
        </a>
        (2006 – present)
       </li>
       <li>
        "
        <a href="http://space.rice.edu/FutureSpace/">
         Future Space
        </a>
        " program (NASA, 2010 - 2013)
       </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
       These projects have resulted in many
       <a href="http://earth.rice.edu/rice_hmns_firsts.html">
        "firsts" in the partnership between Rice and the Houston Museum of Natural Science
       </a>
       .  In addition, Rice has worked with many other outreach partners, including
       <a href="http://www.tsgc.utexas.edu">
        Texas Space Grant
       </a>
       ,
       <a href="http://www.houstonisd.org/">
        HISD
       </a>
       , and Minority Education projects over the years.
      </p>
      <hr class="dotted"/>
      <p>
       These projects have created many educational products (software and planetarium shows).  The only ones that are still distributed by Rice University are the software suites:
      </p>
      <ul>
       <li>
        <a href="http://mms.rice.edu/mms/spaceweather_software.php">
         Space Weather
        </a>
        (initially developed by the POETRY program and still supported by MMS)
        <ul>
         <li class="sublinks noborder">
          <a href="http://mms.rice.edu/mms/forecast.php">
           Space Weather : Forecast
          </a>
          - current and predicted  conditions
         </li>
         <li class="sublinks noborder">
          <a href="http://mms.rice.edu/mms/realtime.php">
           Space Weather : Realtime
          </a>
          - realtime  satellite data
         </li>
         <li class="sublinks">
          <a href="http://mms.rice.edu/mms/spaceweather_resources.php">
           Space Weather : Resources
          </a>
          -  online and downloadable educational  resources
         </li>
        </ul>
       </li>
       <li>
        and the online version of "
        <a href="http://earth.rice.edu/earthupdate/">
         Earth Update
        </a>
        "
       </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
       The other software titles and planetarium shows are now commercially distributed by our spinoff companies Space Update, Inc. and MTPE, Inc. (dba ePlanetarium).
      </p>
      <ul>
       <li>
        <a href="http://www.spaceupdate.com/software_spaceupdate.php">
         Space Update
        </a>
        (from the Public Connection)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://www.spaceupdate.com/software_earthupdate.php#earthupdate">
         Earth Update
        </a>
        (from Museums Teaching Planet Earth)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://www.eplanetarium.com/shows/ddome/force_five/">
         "Force 5"
        </a>
        Planetarium Show (from Museums Teaching Planet Earth)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://www.eplanetarium.com">
         Discovery Dome
        </a>
        portable planetarium system (from Immersive Earth)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://www.eplanetarium.com/shows/ddome/earths_wild_ride/">
         "Earth's Wild Ride"
        </a>
        Planetarium Show  (From Immersive Earth)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://www.eplanetarium.com/shows/ddome/dinosaur_prophecy/">
         "Dinosaur Prophecy"
        </a>
        Planetarium Show  (From Immersive Earth)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://www.eplanetarium.com/shows/ddome/impact_earth/">
         "Impact Earth"
        </a>
        and
        <a href="http://www.eplanetarium.com/shows/ddome/impact/">
         "Impact!"
        </a>
        Planetarium Show  (From Immersive Earth)
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://www.eplanetarium.com/shows/ddome/we_choose_space/">
         "We Choose Space"
        </a>
        (from "Future Space")
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="http://www.eplanetarium.com/shows/ddome/great_planet_adventures/">
         "The Great Planet Adventures"
        </a>
        (from "Future Space")
       </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
       This website archives some of the history and products of our various programs and provides links to our current educational activities.
      </p>
      <!-- END CONTENT -->
